{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect parameter types in generate_srs function declarations\n\n### Summary\nThe LTE SRS (Sounding Reference Signal) generation function had inconsistent parameter types between its implementation and header file declarations. The actual implementation in `srs_modulation.c` expects `int32_t*` for the txdataF parameter, but the header files declared it as `int*`. This mismatch could cause issues on systems where `int` and `int32_t` have different sizes or alignment requirements.\n\nThe issue was identified when tracing through the `lte_srs_channel_estimation` function which calls `generate_srs` with `&srs_vars->srs[eNB_id]` - a pointer to `int32_t`.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/transport_common_proto.h`: Updated generate_srs function signature to use int32_t* instead of int* for txdataF parameter\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/transport_proto_ue.h`: Applied same correction to maintain consistency across header files\n\n"
}